1
00:00:41,917 --> 00:00:45,963
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

2
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:53,262
<i>Grand Prince Cheongheon is</i>
<i>hereby confined to his quarters.</i>

3
00:01:07,025 --> 00:01:08,360
Who goes there?

4
00:01:09,528 --> 00:01:11,905
I have brought you porridge.

5
00:01:11,989 --> 00:01:13,949
Please eat before it gets cold.

6
00:01:16,660 --> 00:01:17,661
It is you.

7
00:01:17,744 --> 00:01:19,913
Have you no fear coming here?

8
00:01:19,997 --> 00:01:21,790
If anyone sees you…

9
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:28,672
I cannot discern
where falsehood ends and truth begins.

10
00:01:28,755 --> 00:01:31,258
The uncertainty leaves me
helpless with dread.

11
00:01:32,384 --> 00:01:34,052
Please enlighten me.

12
00:01:35,721 --> 00:01:37,472
What is the truth?

13
00:01:43,729 --> 00:01:45,272
How could one be so naive?

14
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:48,358
This is why you so easily fall prey
to exploitative men.

15
00:01:48,442 --> 00:01:49,568
Pardon?

16
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:51,445
Do nothing.

17
00:01:54,615 --> 00:01:55,866
Find your path to survive,

18
00:01:55,949 --> 00:01:58,493
just as you did
at the royal interrogation.

19
00:01:58,577 --> 00:01:59,745
This is…

20
00:02:01,663 --> 00:02:03,165
my final command to you.

21
00:02:13,925 --> 00:02:15,135
Kang Dan-sim.

22
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:20,974
Never…

23
00:02:26,355 --> 00:02:27,981
set foot in this place again.

24
00:03:24,496 --> 00:03:25,664
Who…

25
00:03:27,999 --> 00:03:28,959
are you really?

26
00:03:30,293 --> 00:03:31,628
Dan-sim of the Kang clan.

27
00:03:32,713 --> 00:03:33,880
What did you just…

28
00:03:35,757 --> 00:03:37,008
Who are you?

29
00:03:42,556 --> 00:03:44,641
What sort of question is that?

30
00:03:44,725 --> 00:03:45,809
Have you been day-drinking?

31
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:47,185
Raving in broad daylight.

32
00:03:47,269 --> 00:03:49,896
A woman keeps appearing in my dreams.

33
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:50,939
A court lady

34
00:03:51,022 --> 00:03:52,816
with no friends or family.

35
00:03:54,651 --> 00:03:56,695
At first, I thought it was just a dream.

36
00:03:56,778 --> 00:03:58,572
But it's strange.

37
00:03:59,281 --> 00:04:00,949
Because I feel like

38
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:03,160
that woman might be you.

39
00:04:16,006 --> 00:04:17,090
Have I lost my mind?

40
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:22,763
At least you know it sounds crazy.

41
00:04:23,638 --> 00:04:25,515
You're mistaking
nonsense dreams for reality.

42
00:04:25,599 --> 00:04:27,392
- A nonsense dream?
- Yes, a nonsense dream.

43
00:04:28,477 --> 00:04:30,479
Showing up dressed like that,
rambling about dreams?

44
00:04:30,562 --> 00:04:32,898
You have most certainly lost your mind.

45
00:04:33,607 --> 00:04:36,234
I shall go on ahead.
Come back when you are decent.

46
00:04:46,495 --> 00:04:52,667
EPISODE 9
THAT'S FIRST LOVE FOR YOU

47
00:05:01,092 --> 00:05:03,261
- How should we proceed?
- Follow him.

48
00:05:12,646 --> 00:05:13,647
<i>Who…</i>

49
00:05:14,731 --> 00:05:16,316
<i>are you really?</i>

50
00:05:16,399 --> 00:05:18,777
A woman keeps appearing in my dreams.

51
00:05:19,402 --> 00:05:20,612
A court lady…

52
00:05:22,113 --> 00:05:24,157
with no friends or family.

53
00:05:30,789 --> 00:05:32,165
<i>A dream?</i>

54
00:05:53,562 --> 00:05:56,022
Mr. Cha, this launch is a huge success.

55
00:05:56,106 --> 00:05:58,233
If I'd known you'd hit
a home run like this,

56
00:05:58,316 --> 00:06:00,527
I would've invested early on.

57
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:02,028
I couldn't agree more.

58
00:06:02,112 --> 00:06:04,281
At this rate, you could even break
into the US market

59
00:06:04,364 --> 00:06:06,533
and dominate the whole industry.

60
00:06:06,616 --> 00:06:08,535
No need to be intimidated already.

61
00:06:08,618 --> 00:06:10,328
I'll be sure to leave some scraps.

62
00:06:20,672 --> 00:06:22,465
<i>At least you know it sounds crazy.</i>

63
00:06:22,549 --> 00:06:24,426
You're mistaking
nonsense dreams for reality.

64
00:06:37,856 --> 00:06:40,191
- Hello. Hi there.
- Hello.

65
00:06:48,909 --> 00:06:49,826
Can I ask

66
00:06:49,910 --> 00:06:52,704
why you have been trailing me
like a shadow since we arrived?

67
00:06:52,787 --> 00:06:54,205
Well?

68
00:06:54,289 --> 00:06:56,124
You should be working the room.

69
00:06:56,207 --> 00:06:58,877
Do what you can
to land yourself another ad.

70
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,587
Not really my jurisdiction.

71
00:07:00,670 --> 00:07:01,630
Your jurisdiction?

72
00:07:01,713 --> 00:07:03,506
Why would I hawk my face like some peddler

73
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:05,133
if I have an agency?

74
00:07:05,216 --> 00:07:06,259
What do I pay you for?

75
00:07:06,343 --> 00:07:08,303
You can forget about making easy money.

76
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:14,517
That brat always has to have
the last word.

77
00:07:23,276 --> 00:07:24,444
- Shin Seo-ri.
- Gosh!

78
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:28,156
I've been looking everywhere for you.

79
00:07:28,698 --> 00:07:29,824
Are you doing okay?

80
00:07:30,617 --> 00:07:31,952
Don't worry about it.

81
00:07:32,619 --> 00:07:33,954
Just a nonsense dream, remember?

82
00:07:34,037 --> 00:07:36,081
It left me feeling incredibly unsettled.

83
00:07:36,915 --> 00:07:39,292
Choi Mun-do just had to show up too.

84
00:07:39,376 --> 00:07:41,962
He was like a budding tyrant in my dream.

85
00:07:42,045 --> 00:07:44,965
I guess dreams really are
an extension of consciousness.

86
00:07:45,048 --> 00:07:46,758
<i>Maybe it was not just a dream?</i>

87
00:07:47,300 --> 00:07:49,260
<i>Could he really be seeing the past?</i>

88
00:07:50,428 --> 00:07:52,597
Here you are, Se-gye.

89
00:08:02,065 --> 00:08:04,484
Does it just go in one ear
and out the other with you?

90
00:08:04,567 --> 00:08:07,487
I clearly told you to go
through my office until the engagement--

91
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:09,447
What if someone hears you?

92
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:11,658
You're right.

93
00:08:11,741 --> 00:08:13,952
I wasn't thinking. I'll be more careful.

94
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:17,414
You can't be serious, Se-gye.

95
00:08:17,497 --> 00:08:19,749
In public, I'm still your--

96
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:21,543
Yes, you are his fiancée. That you are.

97
00:08:21,626 --> 00:08:22,877
My ears are about to bleed.

98
00:08:22,961 --> 00:08:25,755
Cha Se-gye, I will allow it.
Go hold hands and take a lap.

99
00:08:25,839 --> 00:08:28,133
Even dying wishes are honored.
She is not asking for much.

100
00:08:28,216 --> 00:08:30,385
Go on. Grant her her last wish.

101
00:08:30,468 --> 00:08:33,013
Who are you to give him permission?

102
00:08:33,096 --> 00:08:34,472
You are seriously so exhausting.

103
00:08:34,556 --> 00:08:36,766
Goodness, you're all already here.

104
00:08:37,267 --> 00:08:39,394
Grandfather, what brings you here?

105
00:08:39,477 --> 00:08:42,397
This is my grandson's brand launch.
Why wouldn't I be here?

106
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:44,274
Welcome, Grandfather.

107
00:08:44,858 --> 00:08:46,067
If you had told me beforehand,

108
00:08:46,151 --> 00:08:47,610
I would have escorted you.

109
00:08:48,486 --> 00:08:51,156
Tae-hee, are you already playing the wife?

110
00:08:52,157 --> 00:08:53,366
My Se-gye

111
00:08:53,450 --> 00:08:55,368
is so blessed when it comes to women.

112
00:08:55,452 --> 00:08:56,703
He certainly is.

113
00:08:59,372 --> 00:09:01,374
Grandfather, I need
to introduce you to someone.

114
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:03,460
The official face of Dynaestie
and the key

115
00:09:03,543 --> 00:09:05,170
to our sold-out success. Ms. Shin Seo-ri.

116
00:09:05,253 --> 00:09:07,088
Shin… Shin Seo-ri?

117
00:09:07,172 --> 00:09:08,757
Nice to meet you,

118
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:09,924
Grandpapa!

119
00:09:13,178 --> 00:09:14,137
What the…

120
00:09:15,221 --> 00:09:16,681
Hey, stop it.

121
00:09:16,765 --> 00:09:17,807
Just stop.

122
00:09:17,891 --> 00:09:20,268
- He's not your grandpapa yet.
- He isn't?

123
00:09:20,351 --> 00:09:22,562
Just call him Chairman.

124
00:09:22,645 --> 00:09:24,147
Right.

125
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:26,566
You also badgered me to call you
"Mr. Cha" at the beginning.

126
00:09:26,649 --> 00:09:28,860
I guess being sensitive
about titles like a boomer

127
00:09:28,943 --> 00:09:29,944
is a family trait?

128
00:09:31,946 --> 00:09:32,947
She's a funny one.

129
00:09:33,031 --> 00:09:36,951
So, the model treats the CEO
like her buddy now?

130
00:09:37,035 --> 00:09:38,953
No, it's not like that.

131
00:09:39,037 --> 00:09:40,622
It's like…

132
00:09:40,705 --> 00:09:42,707
You see, she's filming
a historical drama right now.

133
00:09:42,791 --> 00:09:44,709
She's very absorbed in her role.

134
00:09:45,335 --> 00:09:46,586
Method acting, you see.

135
00:09:46,669 --> 00:09:48,463
Chairman Jung is here, sir.

136
00:09:48,546 --> 00:09:50,006
- Over there.
- Chairman Jung. Shall we…

137
00:09:50,090 --> 00:09:51,508
- Chairman Jung is here?
- Yes.

138
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:53,510
Yes, let's go,

139
00:09:53,593 --> 00:09:54,511
Grandfather.

140
00:09:58,181 --> 00:09:59,099
Why, that little…

141
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:03,645
I was just lucky.

142
00:10:04,354 --> 00:10:05,897
Not luck. That's skill.

143
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:08,233
- Stating the obvious.
- Unbelievable.

144
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:10,819
- Good to see you.
- Hello, sir.

145
00:10:10,902 --> 00:10:12,153
- We should get together.
- Sure.

146
00:10:13,696 --> 00:10:16,783
My grandson really hit it big
this time launching Dynaestie.

147
00:10:16,866 --> 00:10:18,284
- He did.
- It must succeed.

148
00:10:18,368 --> 00:10:20,995
Yes, I heard the rumors.
I'm sure he'll do great.

149
00:10:22,705 --> 00:10:26,209
- Well, he's a hard worker, so probably…
- Yes.

150
00:10:27,585 --> 00:10:28,586
With today's launch event,

151
00:10:28,670 --> 00:10:31,131
Mr. Cha's image in the industry
is on the road to recovery.

152
00:10:31,214 --> 00:10:32,423
Response from both the media

153
00:10:32,507 --> 00:10:34,175
and within Chail has been favorable.

154
00:10:34,259 --> 00:10:36,678
It must be the halo effect
from the Chairman.

155
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:38,847
And the anticipation

156
00:10:38,930 --> 00:10:40,640
building around Chail's successor.

157
00:10:41,182 --> 00:10:42,433
What about that nurse?

158
00:10:42,517 --> 00:10:44,352
Is she still unconscious?

159
00:10:44,435 --> 00:10:46,396
Yes, but her medical team
has been paid off,

160
00:10:46,479 --> 00:10:48,356
so they should reach out
if anything changes.

161
00:10:48,439 --> 00:10:50,275
There must be no mistakes this time.

162
00:11:10,086 --> 00:11:12,046
As a court lady in Mr. Cha's dream?

163
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:17,427
If he's seeing the past,

164
00:11:17,510 --> 00:11:19,387
it's not a prophetic dream.

165
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:21,472
Could it be something like reincarnation?

166
00:11:21,556 --> 00:11:23,057
I know you are a seer and all,

167
00:11:23,141 --> 00:11:25,059
but you should still keep up
with the times.

168
00:11:25,143 --> 00:11:27,395
How can you spout such nonsense
in this day and age,

169
00:11:27,478 --> 00:11:28,438
where palanquins fly?

170
00:11:28,521 --> 00:11:30,064
If we can transcend time and space,

171
00:11:30,148 --> 00:11:31,566
why not reincarnation?

172
00:11:31,649 --> 00:11:34,485
If anything, your situation
makes less sense. Seriously.

173
00:11:36,237 --> 00:11:38,573
If it really is reincarnation,

174
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:40,742
do you have anyone you suspect he is?

175
00:11:47,248 --> 00:11:50,043
You said that a man
named Choi Mun-do was the king.

176
00:11:50,126 --> 00:11:53,296
Then wouldn't Mr. Cha
be someone close to him too?

177
00:11:54,547 --> 00:11:56,382
<i>Your dreams have a storyline?</i>

178
00:11:56,466 --> 00:11:58,259
Have you been under stress lately?

179
00:11:58,343 --> 00:11:59,469
How could I not be?

180
00:11:59,552 --> 00:12:01,221
I'm surrounded by minefields.

181
00:12:01,304 --> 00:12:03,514
Never mind that.
Just prescribe me more sleeping pills.

182
00:12:03,598 --> 00:12:04,557
To knock me out cold.

183
00:12:04,641 --> 00:12:07,936
That's not something
you can suppress just by sheer will.

184
00:12:08,019 --> 00:12:10,021
Just relax and go with the flow.

185
00:12:10,104 --> 00:12:11,898
Who knows? It could be a prophetic dream.

186
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:13,399
A prophetic dream…

187
00:12:13,483 --> 00:12:16,736
Are you even listening to me?
And you call yourself a doctor.

188
00:12:16,819 --> 00:12:18,529
It's not the future. It's the past.

189
00:12:18,613 --> 00:12:20,114
Who cares if it's the past or future?

190
00:12:20,198 --> 00:12:21,991
It's still all connected to the present.

191
00:12:22,075 --> 00:12:24,619
You shouldn't assume time is linear.

192
00:12:24,702 --> 00:12:27,080
There could be parallel timelines.

193
00:12:27,163 --> 00:12:28,456
Did you join a cult?

194
00:12:32,001 --> 00:12:34,879
I didn't expect the Chairman
to make a personal appearance.

195
00:12:35,588 --> 00:12:37,548
It's safe to see this as a signal, right?

196
00:12:37,632 --> 00:12:38,508
A signal?

197
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:41,177
Yeah, I guess it's safe
to call it a signal from the brain.

198
00:12:41,261 --> 00:12:44,264
For what feels like an eternity,
I've been waiting

199
00:12:44,347 --> 00:12:46,683
for him to summon us back
to headquarters and finally--

200
00:12:46,766 --> 00:12:48,309
I <i>did</i> wait for an eternity.

201
00:12:48,393 --> 00:12:50,144
It was so bad I even dreamed about it.

202
00:12:50,228 --> 00:12:51,938
Our commute will be a bit longer,

203
00:12:52,021 --> 00:12:54,065
but who cares? We can just sleep less.

204
00:12:54,148 --> 00:12:56,150
Yeah. I haven't been sleeping much lately.

205
00:12:57,110 --> 00:12:59,028
You could call it a symptom
of sleep deprivation.

206
00:12:59,112 --> 00:13:02,031
You know, you can be
so insightful sometimes, Mr. Son.

207
00:13:02,115 --> 00:13:03,449
Yes, sir.

208
00:13:03,992 --> 00:13:06,828
Then, how about a vacation
as a reward before we return…

209
00:13:06,911 --> 00:13:08,037
Sure, go ahead.

210
00:13:08,121 --> 00:13:10,331
Actually, you can take PTO when I do.

211
00:13:10,415 --> 00:13:11,916
Sure. When would that be?

212
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,042
When I'm dead.

213
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:23,678
What's wrong?

214
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:26,514
My teeth have been a bit sensitive lately.
My gums are throbbing.

215
00:13:26,597 --> 00:13:29,559
Even if you skip taking PTO,
you shouldn't skip the dentist.

216
00:13:29,642 --> 00:13:32,145
If left untreated,
dental problems can snowball quickly.

217
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:34,022
The dentist?

218
00:13:38,109 --> 00:13:40,778
Sir, here are the documents to sign

219
00:13:41,654 --> 00:13:43,114
and the script.

220
00:13:43,197 --> 00:13:44,449
<i>The Women's Kingdom?</i>

221
00:13:46,534 --> 00:13:48,619
Oh right. The one with Shin Seo-ri?

222
00:13:48,703 --> 00:13:50,955
Their marketing team proposed
product placement.

223
00:13:51,039 --> 00:13:53,249
But TV shows barely offer
worthwhile ad exposure anymore.

224
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:55,793
I said we'd pass. You can just skip it.

225
00:13:55,877 --> 00:13:57,086
"Consummation"?

226
00:13:57,170 --> 00:13:58,588
CONSUMMATION ON A RAINY NIGHT

227
00:13:58,671 --> 00:14:00,089
Come now, stay still.

228
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:01,382
I am embarrassed.

229
00:14:01,466 --> 00:14:04,385
- Come now, come here…
- Your Majesty.

230
00:14:04,469 --> 00:14:06,054
Why are you in such a hurry?

231
00:14:06,137 --> 00:14:07,847
What is there to be so shy about?

232
00:14:07,930 --> 00:14:10,391
One would think you
a blushing bride on her wedding night.

233
00:14:10,475 --> 00:14:12,435
- Come here.
- Your Majesty.

234
00:14:12,518 --> 00:14:14,145
Please put out the lights first.

235
00:14:15,313 --> 00:14:16,189
Right.

236
00:14:25,823 --> 00:14:28,284
I will not put out the lights tonight.

237
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:30,620
I wish to see
every part of you in <i>full light.</i>

238
00:14:30,703 --> 00:14:32,538
Your Majesty!

239
00:14:33,664 --> 00:14:35,208
Your Majesty!

240
00:14:36,834 --> 00:14:38,586
This is bull…

241
00:14:41,089 --> 00:14:42,256
I'm sorry!

242
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:44,092
I was feeling sleepy, so I took a sip.

243
00:14:44,175 --> 00:14:46,636
- Damn it. I'm so pissed off!
- So sorry I had the coffee.

244
00:14:46,719 --> 00:14:47,804
Mr. Son,

245
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:50,973
get in touch with whoever is
in charge of product placement right now.

246
00:14:51,057 --> 00:14:52,934
Come on, Assistant Director.

247
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:55,603
You can't just cut a whole scene
without even a heads-up.

248
00:14:55,686 --> 00:14:56,813
What are we supposed to do?

249
00:14:56,896 --> 00:14:59,899
It was an urgent request
from one of our partners.

250
00:14:59,982 --> 00:15:01,234
And the substantial amount

251
00:15:01,317 --> 00:15:02,610
led him to make accommodations.

252
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:04,487
No accommodations were made for us.

253
00:15:04,570 --> 00:15:06,280
That's just colluding behind closed doors.

254
00:15:06,364 --> 00:15:07,740
Have her memorize the new script.

255
00:15:07,824 --> 00:15:10,284
This was totally avoidable
with proper writing from the start.

256
00:15:10,368 --> 00:15:12,745
Why are you here,
barking orders to memorize it?

257
00:15:13,996 --> 00:15:15,123
What was it replaced with?

258
00:15:15,206 --> 00:15:16,833
The Sericulture Rite scene.

259
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:18,501
What? The Sericulture Rite?

260
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:20,837
Seri? Siri? Sherry?

261
00:15:24,715 --> 00:15:26,759
THE WOMEN'S KINGDOM 2
BIOJEI REVISED SCRIPT

262
00:15:52,577 --> 00:15:54,579
Lunacy has struck the Inner Court.

263
00:15:54,662 --> 00:15:56,581
This rite is the Queen's authority alone.

264
00:15:56,664 --> 00:15:58,124
Who is she to step in?

265
00:15:58,207 --> 00:16:00,626
What can we do?
The Queen is indisposed with indigestion.

266
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:02,670
It is not like we can postpone it.

267
00:16:18,895 --> 00:16:21,230
Oh my. Look at that. A butterfly.

268
00:16:21,314 --> 00:16:24,025
I kept catching a lovely scent.

269
00:16:24,108 --> 00:16:25,610
It must have been Lady Jang's scent.

270
00:16:25,693 --> 00:16:27,987
Even her skin is as flawless
as white jade.

271
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:30,364
They say she who commands
the finest complexion

272
00:16:30,448 --> 00:16:32,116
commands the palace.

273
00:16:38,915 --> 00:16:40,249
<i>By the time the stormy seas settle</i>

274
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:41,876
<i>Into stillness,</i>

275
00:16:41,959 --> 00:16:45,505
<i>On such a day, shall I expect you to come</i>
<i>from beyond that hill yonder?</i>

276
00:16:46,464 --> 00:16:49,133
<i>Jeweled sunlight on a memorial day</i>
<i>is beautiful.</i>

277
00:16:50,176 --> 00:16:51,594
<i>Even more beautiful still…</i>

278
00:16:53,513 --> 00:16:55,556
<i>Is the luminous texture of your skin.</i>

279
00:16:56,933 --> 00:16:58,309
Biojei.

280
00:16:59,310 --> 00:17:01,103
Cut! That was great.

281
00:17:01,187 --> 00:17:02,688
So good.

282
00:17:03,481 --> 00:17:05,399
Great work, everyone. Good job.

283
00:17:06,817 --> 00:17:08,069
- Oh, dear.
- My shoulder.

284
00:17:09,612 --> 00:17:12,323
Have the writer
and director both gone crazy?

285
00:17:12,406 --> 00:17:14,033
Who sends a revision notice on the day of?

286
00:17:14,116 --> 00:17:18,371
Well, that product placement deal
that just came in was massive.

287
00:17:18,454 --> 00:17:21,624
You know historical dramas
are always tight on budget.

288
00:17:21,707 --> 00:17:24,335
<i>If this can cover the deficit, we should--</i>

289
00:17:24,418 --> 00:17:27,088
Yeah, but why did they have
to replace my solo scene to do that?

290
00:17:27,171 --> 00:17:28,214
It's so annoying.

291
00:17:29,006 --> 00:17:31,884
Then you should've volunteered
for the product placement from the start.

292
00:17:31,968 --> 00:17:35,263
I'm not insane.
Why would I shoot an ad for free?

293
00:17:35,346 --> 00:17:36,556
For Shin Seo-ri's company?

294
00:17:36,639 --> 00:17:39,433
You know, you always snap whenever
Shin Seo-ri is mentioned.

295
00:17:39,517 --> 00:17:41,143
Could that be an inferiority complex?

296
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:43,271
Why the hell would I feel
that way about her?

297
00:17:43,354 --> 00:17:44,397
Damn it.

298
00:17:53,072 --> 00:17:54,073
Cut!

299
00:17:54,156 --> 00:17:55,700
Okay!

300
00:17:56,659 --> 00:17:58,202
Seo-ri, that was great.

301
00:18:01,330 --> 00:18:02,794
I heard she's an acting prodigy.

302
00:18:02,894 --> 00:18:04,750
She has such good diction.

303
00:18:04,834 --> 00:18:06,711
Our director hit the jackpot.

304
00:18:07,295 --> 00:18:08,504
She's really something else.

305
00:18:26,439 --> 00:18:28,399
Why would I ever…

306
00:18:29,442 --> 00:18:31,652
Even on break, make sure you eat properly.

307
00:18:31,736 --> 00:18:34,155
You're on the smaller side for your age,
so eating well matters.

308
00:18:34,238 --> 00:18:35,865
<i>Hey, Dad.</i>

309
00:18:35,948 --> 00:18:38,117
<i>Can I come for a visit?</i>

310
00:18:41,662 --> 00:18:44,540
<i>I've been telling the nanny</i>
<i>for a while now</i>

311
00:18:44,624 --> 00:18:46,542
<i>that I want to visit you.</i>

312
00:18:46,626 --> 00:18:48,461
Seo-jun, you know how busy I am.

313
00:18:49,086 --> 00:18:51,922
Even if you come to Korea,
I don't have time to play.

314
00:18:53,007 --> 00:18:54,175
Seo-jun.

315
00:19:25,498 --> 00:19:27,917
Please book me a ticket
to the US for this weekend.

316
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:30,503
For an early Friday morning flight.

317
00:19:42,515 --> 00:19:43,933
Yeah.

318
00:19:50,272 --> 00:19:53,025
Sir, we just got a call from the hospital.

319
00:20:01,951 --> 00:20:03,828
How could they lose a patient?

320
00:20:03,911 --> 00:20:05,121
An unconscious one, no less.

321
00:20:05,204 --> 00:20:07,623
She was definitely unconscious
during the rounds.

322
00:20:07,707 --> 00:20:08,874
What about CCTV?

323
00:20:08,958 --> 00:20:10,459
No idea where she went?

324
00:20:10,543 --> 00:20:12,878
She took a taxi from the main gate.

325
00:20:12,962 --> 00:20:15,089
We're tracking her likely whereabouts now.

326
00:20:16,006 --> 00:20:17,800
Find her location as quickly as possible.

327
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:20,761
She must be kept
from making any outside contact.

328
00:20:20,845 --> 00:20:22,972
Especially the Chairman or Se-gye.

329
00:20:24,807 --> 00:20:26,726
Look at Shin Seo-ri's quick thinking.

330
00:20:26,809 --> 00:20:28,769
Your acrostic improv earlier was amazing.

331
00:20:30,020 --> 00:20:31,731
I had to do it either way.

332
00:20:31,814 --> 00:20:34,191
They were even getting
a butterfly to land.

333
00:20:34,275 --> 00:20:35,317
No point in holding back.

334
00:20:38,612 --> 00:20:41,031
- Want one?
- Hard candy?

335
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:46,412
A sweet reward after hard work.

336
00:20:49,665 --> 00:20:51,208
Seo-ri!

337
00:20:51,292 --> 00:20:53,252
- Amazing.
- Director.

338
00:20:53,335 --> 00:20:54,628
That last take was really great.

339
00:20:54,712 --> 00:20:57,798
Actors absolutely loathe shooting
product placement these days.

340
00:20:57,882 --> 00:20:59,091
Since they all loathe it so,

341
00:20:59,175 --> 00:21:01,341
I suppose a nobody like me
has no choice but to step up.

342
00:21:01,427 --> 00:21:03,471
No, not at all.
That's a misunderstanding.

343
00:21:03,554 --> 00:21:05,055
The CEO of our partner company

344
00:21:05,139 --> 00:21:08,184
asked for you specifically. Come on now.

345
00:21:09,351 --> 00:21:10,352
The CEO himself?

346
00:21:10,436 --> 00:21:12,354
That's what I'm telling you.

347
00:21:12,438 --> 00:21:14,774
The CEO himself. Amazing.

348
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:34,960
If you want something done,
do it yourself.

349
00:21:36,378 --> 00:21:39,006
The bedroom scene
was definitely cut, right?

350
00:21:46,514 --> 00:21:47,473
Hey, you there.

351
00:21:48,224 --> 00:21:49,558
Hold on a second.

352
00:21:52,603 --> 00:21:53,813
- Who are you?
- Me?

353
00:21:53,896 --> 00:21:57,107
I'm a major investor in this drama.
I had a question for you.

354
00:21:58,108 --> 00:22:00,653
Your bedroom scene
with Shin Seo-ri was cut, right?

355
00:22:03,489 --> 00:22:05,574
Mister, you can't just wander in here.

356
00:22:05,658 --> 00:22:07,117
Are you a stalker fan or what?

357
00:22:07,201 --> 00:22:08,077
Hey, Manager!

358
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,704
There will never be
any bedroom scenes in the future.

359
00:22:10,788 --> 00:22:12,665
So avoid any unnecessary physical contact.

360
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:13,791
Right, so who are you?

361
00:22:13,874 --> 00:22:15,042
Me?

362
00:22:19,171 --> 00:22:20,047
Her stalker fan.

363
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:25,094
Right.

364
00:22:26,804 --> 00:22:27,847
Yeah.

365
00:22:44,947 --> 00:22:47,992
You cannot keep barging in
unannounced like this.

366
00:22:48,075 --> 00:22:49,660
Are you trying to be a hoodlum?

367
00:22:49,743 --> 00:22:50,953
No, it's nothing like that.

368
00:22:51,036 --> 00:22:52,872
I've been stressing over
every little thing,

369
00:22:52,955 --> 00:22:55,416
to the extent I'm having stress dreams.

370
00:22:55,499 --> 00:22:57,209
It's time to start living as I please.

371
00:22:57,293 --> 00:22:59,253
Are you not doing that already?

372
00:22:59,336 --> 00:23:00,504
Changing people's scripts…

373
00:23:00,588 --> 00:23:03,215
That script saw a few edits,
thanks to me, right?

374
00:23:03,299 --> 00:23:04,592
A few?

375
00:23:04,675 --> 00:23:07,177
From what I heard, the male lead
has a terrible reputation.

376
00:23:07,261 --> 00:23:09,096
He ruins kiss scenes on purpose

377
00:23:09,179 --> 00:23:11,181
and bugs his co-stars privately
to run lines off-set.

378
00:23:11,265 --> 00:23:13,183
He's the biggest creep ever.

379
00:23:13,267 --> 00:23:15,060
I was just protecting my actor…

380
00:23:15,895 --> 00:23:18,689
Wait, why am I
making excuses right now?

381
00:23:18,772 --> 00:23:20,649
If anything, <i>you</i> should be thanking me.

382
00:23:20,733 --> 00:23:22,234
Yes, thank you very much.

383
00:23:22,318 --> 00:23:24,528
Thanks to you, I totally stole that scene.

384
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,452
Just with words?

385
00:23:35,247 --> 00:23:36,957
Here, eat this.

386
00:23:38,918 --> 00:23:40,628
I absolutely hate sweets.

387
00:23:40,711 --> 00:23:42,421
- Don't eat it then.
- Come on now.

388
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:47,468
Sickeningly sweet.

389
00:23:48,886 --> 00:23:50,179
Look at this drool. Gross.

390
00:23:59,521 --> 00:24:00,522
Let's create

391
00:24:00,606 --> 00:24:02,816
a position for Se-gye in the company.

392
00:24:02,900 --> 00:24:06,153
We can't keep him
out there forever, can we?

393
00:24:06,236 --> 00:24:07,947
You should ask Se-gye what he thinks, too.

394
00:24:08,030 --> 00:24:10,240
A startup that size
alongside a role here will be hard.

395
00:24:10,324 --> 00:24:13,577
He can leave Biojei to a professional CEO.

396
00:24:13,661 --> 00:24:16,330
He can do anything
if he sets his mind to it.

397
00:24:22,920 --> 00:24:25,339
Is there anywhere
you want to go with me?

398
00:24:25,422 --> 00:24:26,382
Anywhere I want to go?

399
00:24:27,925 --> 00:24:30,260
We've never been on a proper date before.

400
00:24:31,095 --> 00:24:32,179
Let's see.

401
00:24:32,972 --> 00:24:35,140
A good place to go at this hour…

402
00:24:38,560 --> 00:24:40,104
Degeneracy comes so naturally to you.

403
00:24:40,187 --> 00:24:41,855
What is with that look?

404
00:24:41,939 --> 00:24:43,190
No, my tooth actually hurts.

405
00:24:44,858 --> 00:24:46,819
You should have let the sweet
melt in your mouth.

406
00:24:46,902 --> 00:24:48,904
Chomping like that?
Your teeth don't stand a chance.

407
00:24:48,988 --> 00:24:50,614
Melt it? So tedious.

408
00:24:50,698 --> 00:24:52,074
You should savor the good things.

409
00:24:53,075 --> 00:24:55,244
The rich don't know how
to cherish and savor anything.

410
00:24:55,327 --> 00:24:56,704
That's not true.

411
00:24:58,789 --> 00:25:01,583
I cherish you a lot.
I don't chew you up all at once.

412
00:25:06,964 --> 00:25:09,258
Wait. Blood! There is blood!

413
00:25:09,341 --> 00:25:10,676
Blood? What blood?

414
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:23,522
Well…

415
00:25:27,443 --> 00:25:29,361
His complexion is fine. It is not poison.

416
00:25:29,445 --> 00:25:31,071
Since he is bleeding and in pain,

417
00:25:31,155 --> 00:25:32,656
I suspect it is a tooth of wisdom.

418
00:25:32,740 --> 00:25:33,907
The <i>Dongui Bogam</i> prescribes

419
00:25:33,991 --> 00:25:37,619
a mixture of calcined chicken droppings
and straw shoes, along with deer musk.

420
00:25:37,703 --> 00:25:38,787
Droppings and straw shoes?

421
00:25:38,871 --> 00:25:40,330
What are you dawdling for?

422
00:25:40,414 --> 00:25:42,958
Your patient is in agony.
At least administer some acupuncture!

423
00:25:43,042 --> 00:25:44,585
- I'm not in that much pain.
- Stop.

424
00:25:44,668 --> 00:25:46,253
What does the patient know? Stay still.

425
00:25:46,336 --> 00:25:47,546
Calm down, Shin Seo-ri.

426
00:25:47,629 --> 00:25:48,964
It's an impacted wisdom tooth.

427
00:25:49,048 --> 00:25:50,174
You're going to need surgery.

428
00:25:50,257 --> 00:25:52,384
- "Impacted"?
- Just pull it out.

429
00:25:52,468 --> 00:25:54,928
What sort of wisdom tooth
requires surgery?

430
00:25:55,012 --> 00:25:57,347
It depends on the case.

431
00:25:57,431 --> 00:26:00,809
The impacted wisdom tooth on the left
will need to be surgically removed.

432
00:26:00,893 --> 00:26:03,145
So, shall we proceed
with the surgery immediately?

433
00:26:03,228 --> 00:26:04,521
Yes, whatever it takes.

434
00:26:04,605 --> 00:26:06,190
Hurry up and do it. Come on.

435
00:26:06,273 --> 00:26:08,692
- Just a moment.
- This is why I hate the dentist.

436
00:26:08,776 --> 00:26:09,943
Open your mouth. Open.

437
00:26:11,987 --> 00:26:13,822
OPERATING ROOM

438
00:26:15,074 --> 00:26:18,035
Never in my life did I think
I'd be put under for a wisdom tooth.

439
00:26:18,118 --> 00:26:20,162
Good thing we came to a large clinic.

440
00:26:20,245 --> 00:26:22,998
- I saved your precious life again.
- No.

441
00:26:23,082 --> 00:26:25,793
A wisdom tooth isn't
exactly life-threatening.

442
00:26:25,876 --> 00:26:28,879
No time like the present.
Just get it properly treated now.

443
00:26:28,962 --> 00:26:30,714
And let it melt next time.

444
00:26:30,798 --> 00:26:32,299
What? Are you leaving?

445
00:26:32,382 --> 00:26:33,842
It is late. I should get going.

446
00:26:33,926 --> 00:26:36,136
Exactly, it's late.

447
00:26:37,387 --> 00:26:38,639
Just stay.

448
00:26:41,183 --> 00:26:42,518
The post-surgery pain alone…

449
00:26:43,477 --> 00:26:45,187
You said it was not fatal.

450
00:26:45,270 --> 00:26:47,356
Still, I'm getting surgery here.

451
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:50,776
Don't you think abandoning
someone you're seeing is a little rude?

452
00:26:50,859 --> 00:26:54,446
What a novel way of asking me to stay
and wait on you hand and foot.

453
00:26:54,530 --> 00:26:56,615
Let's head in now.

454
00:27:02,955 --> 00:27:03,997
I'm counting on you.

455
00:27:05,124 --> 00:27:06,458
You'd better not leave.

456
00:27:07,709 --> 00:27:09,002
Promise me.

457
00:27:17,427 --> 00:27:19,096
Administering the anesthesia now.

458
00:27:36,113 --> 00:27:37,281
<i>O Heaven.</i>

459
00:27:38,282 --> 00:27:40,951
<i>I want to know you and be known by you.</i>

460
00:27:41,034 --> 00:27:43,203
<i>It shall never fade</i>
<i>as long as life endures.</i>

461
00:27:44,371 --> 00:27:47,499
<i>Until the mountains have no peaks,</i>
<i>and the river waters run dry.</i>

462
00:27:47,583 --> 00:27:49,126
<i>Until the thunder rolls in winter</i>

463
00:27:49,209 --> 00:27:51,253
<i>and the snow falls in the summer.</i>

464
00:27:51,336 --> 00:27:53,046
<i>Until heaven and earth become one.</i>

465
00:27:54,715 --> 00:27:56,884
<i>Only then would I dare to part from you.</i>

466
00:28:10,856 --> 00:28:12,149
This…

467
00:28:13,775 --> 00:28:15,903
I cannot bring myself to deliver.

468
00:28:32,294 --> 00:28:33,879
Sir, are you awake?

469
00:28:36,548 --> 00:28:37,424
Where did she go?

470
00:28:37,507 --> 00:28:40,552
You may experience a sore throat
and a nosebleed from the intubation.

471
00:28:40,636 --> 00:28:44,181
For 48 hours following the extraction,
cold compresses are recommended.

472
00:28:44,264 --> 00:28:47,226
If everything looks good
tomorrow morning, you'll be discharged.

473
00:28:47,309 --> 00:28:48,477
Excuse me.

474
00:28:49,645 --> 00:28:51,104
Did she leave?

475
00:28:51,188 --> 00:28:52,397
Who?

476
00:28:59,821 --> 00:29:01,198
She left.

477
00:29:02,574 --> 00:29:03,909
That heartless woman.

478
00:29:34,815 --> 00:29:36,358
Is that Byeokjo wood?

479
00:29:36,441 --> 00:29:38,110
The lightning-struck jujube tree.

480
00:29:38,193 --> 00:29:39,403
When I was little,

481
00:29:39,486 --> 00:29:41,530
my dad was a peddler.

482
00:29:42,155 --> 00:29:45,659
Sometimes women asked him to get it
to pray for their sick sons.

483
00:29:46,451 --> 00:29:47,995
Who are you praying for?

484
00:29:48,078 --> 00:29:49,997
Your father? Your brother?

485
00:29:51,915 --> 00:29:54,334
Wait, you said you had no family.

486
00:30:16,356 --> 00:30:17,566
Seriously?

487
00:30:19,067 --> 00:30:20,736
I thought you left.

488
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:22,779
You told me not to go.

489
00:30:23,322 --> 00:30:24,698
I went to get some ice.

490
00:30:30,996 --> 00:30:31,872
Hold on.

491
00:30:32,581 --> 00:30:33,623
Your hands are frozen.

492
00:30:34,374 --> 00:30:36,960
You shouldn't have carried that
with your bare hands.

493
00:30:37,044 --> 00:30:39,546
How else would I carry it? On my head?

494
00:30:40,630 --> 00:30:43,050
You said you are hurting.
I had to do something.

495
00:30:44,926 --> 00:30:47,137
This is all I can do for you.

496
00:30:54,311 --> 00:30:55,771
Still, it's too cold.

497
00:30:58,732 --> 00:31:00,025
Stop that!

498
00:31:00,692 --> 00:31:03,320
Patients should just lie still.
That is how you help.

499
00:31:05,989 --> 00:31:07,449
You look just like a pufferfish.

500
00:31:07,532 --> 00:31:09,034
With those puffy cheeks.

501
00:31:11,244 --> 00:31:12,746
You should just go home.

502
00:31:14,122 --> 00:31:16,041
You're enjoying this way too much.

503
00:31:19,503 --> 00:31:23,006
I feel like I keep losing face
ever since we started seeing each other.

504
00:31:35,811 --> 00:31:37,479
About that dream you had…

505
00:31:38,313 --> 00:31:39,648
Have you had any more?

506
00:31:41,691 --> 00:31:42,567
Why?

507
00:31:43,568 --> 00:31:46,655
You said it was nonsense,
but you were clearly bothered by it.

508
00:31:47,280 --> 00:31:50,242
The resemblance must be strong
if it confused you that much.

509
00:31:50,992 --> 00:31:53,120
I began to grow a bit curious.

510
00:31:56,415 --> 00:31:57,582
Well, the dream

511
00:31:58,125 --> 00:31:59,376
is a bit dark.

512
00:32:00,710 --> 00:32:02,087
I anticipate a sad ending.

513
00:32:04,047 --> 00:32:06,425
- "Sad"?
- Yeah, it's about being framed

514
00:32:06,508 --> 00:32:08,510
and locked up. That sort of thing.

515
00:32:09,177 --> 00:32:11,054
Isn't a sad ending inevitable?

516
00:32:11,138 --> 00:32:12,848
I think exile is coming soon too.

517
00:32:13,473 --> 00:32:14,683
Exile…

518
00:32:18,061 --> 00:32:20,230
Then who are you in all this?

519
00:32:20,313 --> 00:32:21,314
Me?

520
00:32:23,233 --> 00:32:25,360
They call me "Your Highness"
or something like that.

521
00:32:25,444 --> 00:32:27,112
"His Highness, the Grand Prince."

522
00:32:28,572 --> 00:32:31,366
I must be a prince
or something like that.

523
00:32:31,450 --> 00:32:32,742
No surprise there.

524
00:32:35,454 --> 00:32:36,788
<i>I should have known</i>

525
00:32:37,372 --> 00:32:39,166
<i>a bad gut feeling is never wrong.</i>

526
00:32:39,916 --> 00:32:41,835
It seemed like that man

527
00:32:41,918 --> 00:32:44,754
felt a certain way about that woman,
the court lady named Kang Dan-sim.

528
00:32:44,838 --> 00:32:46,089
<i>Resentment.</i>

529
00:32:46,715 --> 00:32:47,883
Love…

530
00:32:51,553 --> 00:32:52,721
He felt

531
00:32:53,305 --> 00:32:54,598
a deep yearning for her.

532
00:32:57,642 --> 00:32:58,768
<i>"O Heaven."</i>

533
00:32:59,436 --> 00:33:02,189
<i>"I wish to live forever in your embrace."</i>

534
00:33:02,272 --> 00:33:05,650
<i>"Until the mountains erode</i>
<i>and the rivers run dry."</i>

535
00:33:06,485 --> 00:33:08,028
<i>"Until thunder strikes in winter</i>

536
00:33:08,111 --> 00:33:10,739
<i>and heavy snow falls in summer."</i>

537
00:33:10,822 --> 00:33:13,241
<i>"Until the day heaven</i>
<i>and earth become one."</i>

538
00:33:13,325 --> 00:33:15,327
<i>"Only then shall I part with you."</i>

539
00:33:15,994 --> 00:33:17,120
A whole lot of sentiment.

540
00:33:18,288 --> 00:33:20,665
He was in love with that woman.

541
00:33:20,749 --> 00:33:21,666
Like a fool.

542
00:33:25,378 --> 00:33:27,380
SUCCESSION IN FULL SWING WITH MOCHANG

543
00:33:28,632 --> 00:33:30,175
What's with that dress?

544
00:33:30,258 --> 00:33:31,843
It'll only make you look short.

545
00:33:31,927 --> 00:33:33,637
I told you that you always need

546
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:35,639
a higher waistline because you're short.

547
00:33:35,722 --> 00:33:38,975
You run a business,
yet you still have no sense of style.

548
00:33:40,352 --> 00:33:41,478
It's been a while, Mom.

549
00:33:41,561 --> 00:33:44,105
Still as beautiful
and foul-mouthed as ever.

550
00:33:44,189 --> 00:33:46,149
Is that any way to speak to your mother?

551
00:33:46,233 --> 00:33:48,652
You got back ages ago
but never once came home.

552
00:33:48,735 --> 00:33:50,695
Chasing after him
when you're not even married yet.

553
00:33:50,779 --> 00:33:52,697
I guess I find it more comfortable there.

554
00:33:53,490 --> 00:33:55,367
No one to breathe
down my neck every second.

555
00:33:55,450 --> 00:33:57,077
What?

556
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:58,620
This actually works out.

557
00:33:58,703 --> 00:34:00,622
I wanted to speed things up anyway.

558
00:34:02,332 --> 00:34:03,875
Invite us over.

559
00:34:03,959 --> 00:34:04,918
Se-gye and me.

560
00:34:13,218 --> 00:34:14,844
MOCHANG HEIR
ATTENDS CHA'S BRAND LAUNCH

561
00:34:17,764 --> 00:34:19,933
Look at them
telling the whole world about it.

562
00:34:28,692 --> 00:34:29,859
<i>Ms. Shin,</i>

563
00:34:29,943 --> 00:34:31,653
<i>we should get together soon.</i>

564
00:34:31,736 --> 00:34:33,488
<i>Is it him?</i>

565
00:34:34,739 --> 00:34:36,324
GRANDMA

566
00:34:37,951 --> 00:34:39,327
<i>You don't even have money.</i>

567
00:34:39,411 --> 00:34:40,620
This is way too expensive.

568
00:34:40,704 --> 00:34:42,247
Tell them to change my room right now.

569
00:34:42,330 --> 00:34:45,208
Why would you want
to be packed in like sardines again?

570
00:34:45,292 --> 00:34:46,167
So you can fight?

571
00:34:46,251 --> 00:34:48,128
Fight? Don't be ridiculous.

572
00:34:48,211 --> 00:34:51,798
Those old ladies were just bored
and running their mouths for nothing.

573
00:34:51,881 --> 00:34:53,925
You said you wanted to be discharged soon.

574
00:34:54,009 --> 00:34:55,677
You will recover faster there.

575
00:34:56,428 --> 00:34:57,554
<i>Is it not sunnier there?</i>

576
00:34:57,637 --> 00:34:59,306
<i>Even the air feels different, no?</i>

577
00:35:01,975 --> 00:35:03,059
Not really.

578
00:35:03,143 --> 00:35:04,603
<i>And I have money!</i>

579
00:35:04,686 --> 00:35:06,229
Did you forget I am on TV?

580
00:35:06,313 --> 00:35:09,357
I am making loads of it,
so do not worry about that.

581
00:35:09,441 --> 00:35:11,901
Just eat well
and focus on getting better.

582
00:35:11,985 --> 00:35:14,195
Look at this old lady

583
00:35:14,279 --> 00:35:16,865
living in luxury
thanks to her sweet grandchild.

584
00:35:18,658 --> 00:35:20,201
<i>But Seo-ri,</i>

585
00:35:20,285 --> 00:35:22,704
I like being around people.

586
00:35:23,330 --> 00:35:26,041
Rather than be all alone by yourself,

587
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:30,086
you should have a little bustle around you
to remind you that you're alive.

588
00:35:31,129 --> 00:35:34,049
<i>No matter how great you are,</i>
<i>no one can live completely alone.</i>

589
00:35:34,132 --> 00:35:36,176
Sure, people thrive on feeling superior,

590
00:35:36,259 --> 00:35:37,886
but that's no way to live.

591
00:35:37,969 --> 00:35:40,096
<i>You'll just end up withering away alone.</i>

592
00:35:51,941 --> 00:35:53,943
Hey, remember that young lady

593
00:35:54,027 --> 00:35:55,862
I shared a table with the other day?

594
00:35:55,945 --> 00:35:56,905
Is she a regular?

595
00:35:56,988 --> 00:35:59,532
She is. She's here
two or three times a week.

596
00:35:59,616 --> 00:36:00,575
Why do you ask?

597
00:36:00,659 --> 00:36:03,620
Well, she just left quite an impression.

598
00:36:04,412 --> 00:36:07,332
A young person eating alone like that…

599
00:36:07,415 --> 00:36:09,876
She must have no friends.
Many kids come alone now.

600
00:36:09,959 --> 00:36:11,002
Right.

601
00:36:11,503 --> 00:36:12,629
She has

602
00:36:13,129 --> 00:36:14,130
no friends?

603
00:36:15,674 --> 00:36:16,549
I see.

604
00:36:17,258 --> 00:36:18,885
What do you think of her?

605
00:36:18,968 --> 00:36:20,053
How's her character?

606
00:36:21,221 --> 00:36:22,806
And what's it to you?

607
00:36:22,889 --> 00:36:23,890
Looking for a new wife?

608
00:36:23,973 --> 00:36:26,393
You crazy old hag.
Have you officially gone senile?

609
00:36:27,310 --> 00:36:29,354
Her character is a lost cause.

610
00:36:29,437 --> 00:36:31,314
It's like half her tongue is missing,

611
00:36:31,398 --> 00:36:33,525
dropping all her honorifics
left and right.

612
00:36:36,194 --> 00:36:37,112
I see.

613
00:36:37,654 --> 00:36:38,780
Is that so?

614
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:47,038
<i>No matter how great you are,</i>
<i>no one can live completely alone.</i>

615
00:36:47,122 --> 00:36:48,373
<i>Kang Dan-sim.</i>

616
00:36:48,456 --> 00:36:51,084
Never set foot in this place again.

617
00:36:51,167 --> 00:36:54,754
<i>Sure, people thrive on feeling superior,</i>
<i>but that's no way to live.</i>

618
00:36:54,838 --> 00:36:56,756
<i>You'll just end up withering away alone.</i>

619
00:36:56,840 --> 00:36:59,050
They call me "Your Highness"
or something like that.

620
00:36:59,134 --> 00:37:00,844
"His Highness, the Grand Prince."

621
00:37:02,387 --> 00:37:03,805
You're finally home.

622
00:37:08,184 --> 00:37:09,352
Did you eat?

623
00:37:12,439 --> 00:37:13,898
Enjoy.

624
00:37:18,945 --> 00:37:21,156
So, how are your teeth?

625
00:37:21,239 --> 00:37:22,532
Are you all better now?

626
00:37:22,615 --> 00:37:25,660
Of course.
It was just a wisdom tooth. No big deal.

627
00:37:27,454 --> 00:37:29,289
But you bled so much.

628
00:37:29,387 --> 00:37:31,249
Have yourself some herbal medicine made.

629
00:37:31,332 --> 00:37:33,293
It can only do you good.

630
00:37:33,376 --> 00:37:35,128
Well, you know,

631
00:37:35,211 --> 00:37:37,630
I tend not to rely on stuff like that.

632
00:37:37,714 --> 00:37:38,840
More importantly,

633
00:37:40,300 --> 00:37:42,010
I said let's get a meal. What is this?

634
00:37:42,093 --> 00:37:43,386
We're out on some chaotic street.

635
00:37:43,470 --> 00:37:45,638
I think the bustle is nice.

636
00:37:46,347 --> 00:37:48,308
What if someone recognizes you?

637
00:37:48,391 --> 00:37:49,726
Honestly,

638
00:37:49,809 --> 00:37:52,020
sometimes you just totally forget
you're a celebrity.

639
00:37:52,103 --> 00:37:54,314
And you shouldn't stay out too late.

640
00:37:54,397 --> 00:37:55,690
The streets are dark.

641
00:37:56,191 --> 00:37:57,859
What am I? A kid?

642
00:37:57,942 --> 00:37:58,818
Watching over me…

643
00:38:00,111 --> 00:38:01,696
Why wouldn't I?

644
00:38:01,780 --> 00:38:02,906
We're seeing each other.

645
00:38:02,989 --> 00:38:05,408
Don't I deserve to worry about you?

646
00:38:05,492 --> 00:38:07,160
As if seeing each other is a big deal.

647
00:38:07,243 --> 00:38:09,788
You sure do expect a lot for a trial run.

648
00:38:19,756 --> 00:38:22,258
I'll personally handle Grandfather,

649
00:38:22,342 --> 00:38:23,760
so stop worrying.

650
00:38:25,261 --> 00:38:27,347
And the arranged marriage…

651
00:38:29,891 --> 00:38:32,811
I'll sort all of that out soon enough,

652
00:38:33,686 --> 00:38:34,562
so don't stress.

653
00:38:35,188 --> 00:38:36,940
You want to end it already?

654
00:38:37,023 --> 00:38:38,650
Why not milk it a bit longer?

655
00:38:38,733 --> 00:38:40,401
- What?
- Since you already started,

656
00:38:40,485 --> 00:38:42,028
milk it for all it is worth.

657
00:38:42,111 --> 00:38:45,281
The papers are already saying
how good this is for you.

658
00:38:45,907 --> 00:38:48,117
Why not go all out while you are at it?

659
00:38:48,201 --> 00:38:49,953
No need to tiptoe around me.

660
00:38:50,620 --> 00:38:51,996
I never tiptoed.

661
00:38:52,080 --> 00:38:54,707
I've never once tiptoed
around anyone, ever.

662
00:38:54,791 --> 00:38:57,085
You sure tiptoed like a ballerina
around your grandfather.

663
00:38:57,168 --> 00:38:58,711
It's all talk with you.

664
00:38:58,795 --> 00:39:00,129
I just…

665
00:39:03,883 --> 00:39:05,468
wanted to make you look good.

666
00:39:06,427 --> 00:39:07,303
What?

667
00:39:08,179 --> 00:39:09,556
I did that

668
00:39:10,265 --> 00:39:12,225
so you'd make a good impression on him.

669
00:39:17,730 --> 00:39:19,107
Your grandfather

670
00:39:19,190 --> 00:39:21,276
seemed quite fond of that little schemer.

671
00:39:22,068 --> 00:39:24,696
Then again, she did seem
to have pretty solid backing.

672
00:39:24,779 --> 00:39:25,738
"Little Schemer"?

673
00:39:26,489 --> 00:39:28,157
You gave her a nickname already?

674
00:39:28,992 --> 00:39:30,869
I can't deny that.

675
00:39:31,995 --> 00:39:32,954
But don't worry.

676
00:39:33,037 --> 00:39:34,581
"Backing"?

677
00:39:35,331 --> 00:39:36,541
I don't need any of that.

678
00:39:36,624 --> 00:39:38,585
You know how exceptional I am.

679
00:39:38,668 --> 00:39:40,795
Look at me.
I'm doing great all by myself already.

680
00:39:41,629 --> 00:39:43,548
"Cream rises to the top."

681
00:39:43,631 --> 00:39:46,009
The nail that sticks out
gets hammered down.

682
00:39:46,092 --> 00:39:47,552
If you stand out too much,

683
00:39:48,261 --> 00:39:50,388
you will just wither away all alone.

684
00:39:51,723 --> 00:39:53,892
I have seen it time and time again.

685
00:40:12,076 --> 00:40:13,119
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

686
00:40:15,163 --> 00:40:16,331
Listen.

687
00:40:18,416 --> 00:40:20,376
You need to watch out for Choi Mun-do.

688
00:40:23,004 --> 00:40:24,547
And do not trust anyone.

689
00:40:26,758 --> 00:40:28,885
I can take care of myself.

690
00:40:28,968 --> 00:40:30,970
I told you not to worry.

691
00:40:31,846 --> 00:40:33,264
Do you…

692
00:40:34,349 --> 00:40:36,142
Do you think the world is that easy?

693
00:40:36,225 --> 00:40:37,977
Anyone could be lining up to attack you,

694
00:40:38,061 --> 00:40:39,979
but you're focusing on
taking me out on dates.

695
00:40:40,063 --> 00:40:41,689
Indulging in petty love games?

696
00:40:41,773 --> 00:40:43,441
Yeah, I find the world easy.

697
00:40:43,524 --> 00:40:45,610
It will always be spiraling
into insanity.

698
00:40:45,697 --> 00:40:47,169
Why overcomplicate things?

699
00:40:47,236 --> 00:40:48,655
Regardless of what you think,

700
00:40:48,738 --> 00:40:51,866
if you have no regrets,
you have nothing to lose in this world.

701
00:40:53,952 --> 00:40:54,827
But…

702
00:40:56,245 --> 00:40:57,705
it's you I find difficult.

703
00:40:59,290 --> 00:41:01,459
It's weird.
It gets harder as time goes on.

704
00:41:03,544 --> 00:41:05,505
Maybe it's because I like you so much?

705
00:41:12,261 --> 00:41:13,638
Stop it.

706
00:41:13,721 --> 00:41:14,639
It is pathetic.

707
00:41:14,722 --> 00:41:16,808
So what if I'm a little pathetic?

708
00:41:16,891 --> 00:41:18,893
Then stop showing up in my dreams.

709
00:41:23,231 --> 00:41:24,440
What if…

710
00:41:26,275 --> 00:41:28,069
- it were not a dream?
- What?

711
00:41:28,152 --> 00:41:29,862
What if it were not a dream?

712
00:41:30,780 --> 00:41:31,864
What would you do then?

713
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:34,075
What are you talking about?

714
00:41:35,660 --> 00:41:38,287
The court lady with no family or friends.

715
00:41:38,371 --> 00:41:41,457
The naive girl, cluelessly suffering
through initiation rites.

716
00:41:42,333 --> 00:41:43,376
If I were

717
00:41:43,459 --> 00:41:45,253
that woman, Kang Dan-sim…

718
00:41:47,088 --> 00:41:48,047
what would you do?

719
00:41:50,008 --> 00:41:52,802
If I were that ruthless woman,
solely focused on surviving…

720
00:41:53,803 --> 00:41:55,054
You…

721
00:42:06,024 --> 00:42:07,859
COURT LADY KANG DAN-SIM
NO SEARCH RESULTS

722
00:42:16,451 --> 00:42:18,077
What am I even doing?

723
00:42:36,179 --> 00:42:37,930
MS. SHIN, WE SHOULD GET TOGETHER SOON

724
00:42:38,806 --> 00:42:40,433
<i>It seemed like that man</i>

725
00:42:40,516 --> 00:42:43,227
<i>felt a certain way about that woman,</i>
<i>the court lady named Kang Dan-sim.</i>

726
00:42:43,311 --> 00:42:44,437
Love…

727
00:42:46,647 --> 00:42:48,066
He felt…

728
00:42:50,610 --> 00:42:51,819
a deep yearning for her.

729
00:42:52,528 --> 00:42:54,155
<i>He was in love with that woman.</i>

730
00:42:54,238 --> 00:42:55,615
<i>Like a fool.</i>

731
00:42:56,783 --> 00:42:59,327
<i>I can never truly know if he had</i>

732
00:42:59,911 --> 00:43:01,287
<i>such affections for me.</i>

733
00:43:05,917 --> 00:43:08,044
<i>And even if he did,</i>

734
00:43:08,127 --> 00:43:10,338
<i>what good would it do me now?</i>

735
00:43:11,464 --> 00:43:13,341
TIME TRAVEL TO THE JOSEON DYNASTY

736
00:43:13,424 --> 00:43:15,134
THE GRAND HISTORY: 1392 TO 2026

737
00:43:15,218 --> 00:43:16,969
SEOUL MUSEUM OF HISTORY

738
00:43:30,817 --> 00:43:32,777
<i>Why do you stare at it so intently?</i>

739
00:43:33,486 --> 00:43:37,532
Does a plum blossom flowering
in midsummer unsettle you so?

740
00:43:46,582 --> 00:43:49,127
<i>Back when I painted this,</i>

741
00:43:50,336 --> 00:43:52,672
<i>I had buried him in my heart.</i>

742
00:44:05,059 --> 00:44:05,977
Hold on!

743
00:44:07,145 --> 00:44:09,397
You're that woman from last time, right?

744
00:44:09,480 --> 00:44:10,773
Royal Consort Kang!

745
00:44:11,440 --> 00:44:12,859
Hello.

746
00:44:12,942 --> 00:44:16,946
I'm writing my thesis on reinterpreting
that infamous villainess, you see.

747
00:44:17,029 --> 00:44:18,948
That's why I was so excited
to hear you speak.

748
00:44:19,031 --> 00:44:20,158
Wow.

749
00:44:21,033 --> 00:44:22,785
I guess you're still on that quest.

750
00:44:23,452 --> 00:44:25,079
The story of Royal Consort Kang.

751
00:44:30,001 --> 00:44:34,046
<i>If I were that woman, Kang Dan-sim,</i>
<i>what would you do?</i>

752
00:44:39,427 --> 00:44:40,553
Sir.

753
00:44:40,636 --> 00:44:43,514
I thought you were ready to go,
but you seem lost in your thoughts.

754
00:44:46,267 --> 00:44:48,436
Mr. Son, do you believe in past lives?

755
00:44:48,519 --> 00:44:50,104
Past lives, all of a sudden?

756
00:44:50,188 --> 00:44:51,939
Well, I guess I do.

757
00:44:52,023 --> 00:44:54,192
My family's been Buddhist for generations.

758
00:44:54,275 --> 00:44:55,860
So past lives, reincarnation…

759
00:44:55,943 --> 00:44:57,695
That all makes sense to you?

760
00:44:57,778 --> 00:44:59,113
I don't see why not.

761
00:44:59,197 --> 00:45:00,448
This life is our present life.

762
00:45:00,531 --> 00:45:02,116
In between our past and next lives.

763
00:45:02,200 --> 00:45:04,535
That's the gist of it.
But why the sudden interest?

764
00:45:05,953 --> 00:45:07,413
Well, the thing is…

765
00:45:09,165 --> 00:45:10,917
Hypothetically speaking,

766
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:13,294
if someone said they came from the past,

767
00:45:13,377 --> 00:45:14,295
what would that mean?

768
00:45:14,378 --> 00:45:15,963
When in the past?

769
00:45:17,673 --> 00:45:19,217
It's ridiculous.

770
00:45:19,300 --> 00:45:20,676
- Joseon.
- Joseon?

771
00:45:21,302 --> 00:45:23,763
Did someone from "Joseon"
tell you that your ancestors are angry?

772
00:45:23,846 --> 00:45:26,265
Did they ask for memorial service money?

773
00:45:26,349 --> 00:45:28,684
That's a classic cult recruitment line.

774
00:45:28,768 --> 00:45:29,769
No, it's not like that.

775
00:45:29,852 --> 00:45:31,687
Tell them you have no need
for such ancestors.

776
00:45:31,771 --> 00:45:32,772
No memorial service.

777
00:45:32,855 --> 00:45:34,815
True ancestors bless. Evil spirits harm.

778
00:45:34,899 --> 00:45:36,317
Please come out now.

779
00:45:39,612 --> 00:45:42,281
Damn it, I should never have told her
about the dream.

780
00:45:44,242 --> 00:45:46,410
Now there's a weird wall between us.

781
00:45:49,872 --> 00:45:51,290
You're an actor, right?

782
00:45:51,374 --> 00:45:53,209
<i>The Women's Kingdom 2?</i>

783
00:45:53,292 --> 00:45:54,460
Wow.

784
00:45:54,543 --> 00:45:57,213
No wonder you had such a unique vibe.

785
00:45:57,964 --> 00:46:00,341
You know, after I started interning here,

786
00:46:00,424 --> 00:46:02,051
I discovered something really amazing.

787
00:46:02,134 --> 00:46:04,887
The piece itself isn't fully intact,

788
00:46:04,971 --> 00:46:07,306
so it's not popular with visitors,

789
00:46:07,390 --> 00:46:10,601
but <i>we</i> refer to it as
<i>The Portrait of a Beauty.</i>

790
00:46:11,769 --> 00:46:13,229
Come take a look.

791
00:46:31,914 --> 00:46:33,541
She looks like you, doesn't she?

792
00:46:34,041 --> 00:46:35,918
It's only half a painting,

793
00:46:36,002 --> 00:46:38,713
but no matter how I look at it,
it looks just like you.

794
00:46:38,796 --> 00:46:42,049
I guess doppelgängers really do exist.

795
00:46:49,348 --> 00:46:51,350
But what's even crazier is

796
00:46:51,434 --> 00:46:53,769
that this is actually a love letter.

797
00:46:53,853 --> 00:46:56,188
If you look on the right, there's a poem.

798
00:46:56,897 --> 00:46:58,065
<i>O Heaven.</i>

799
00:46:58,858 --> 00:47:01,569
And it's not just any paper.
It's drawn on precious mulberry paper.

800
00:47:01,652 --> 00:47:04,613
Seeing as they painted this
and even wrote a love letter,

801
00:47:04,697 --> 00:47:07,366
this was no ordinary crush.

802
00:47:07,450 --> 00:47:11,078
It's like the ultimate unspoken love.

803
00:47:12,038 --> 00:47:13,080
Isn't it so romantic?

804
00:47:15,041 --> 00:47:17,543
A gift for my dearest companion.

805
00:47:32,933 --> 00:47:37,021
- It is the Grand Prince.
- Hey, make way!

806
00:47:37,104 --> 00:47:40,900
He is not just any royal.
He is a full brother to the Crown Prince.

807
00:47:40,983 --> 00:47:43,235
Gosh, he is quite a looker.

808
00:47:43,319 --> 00:47:44,820
Is he not?

809
00:47:44,904 --> 00:47:47,239
I heard he is quite the womanizer.

810
00:47:47,323 --> 00:47:49,367
Just look at that pretty-boy face.

811
00:48:34,829 --> 00:48:36,747
And what happens after you follow him?

812
00:48:36,831 --> 00:48:38,624
Will you two run away together?

813
00:48:41,502 --> 00:48:43,379
Right, keep your mouth shut.

814
00:48:43,462 --> 00:48:47,091
Bury your feelings deep in your heart.
That is the only way to survive.

815
00:48:48,843 --> 00:48:49,802
Take it.

816
00:48:52,596 --> 00:48:55,307
This is from me, not the Grand Prince.

817
00:48:55,933 --> 00:48:58,102
May this serve as the token
of your lone survival.

818
00:49:38,893 --> 00:49:40,436
But still…

819
00:49:42,104 --> 00:49:43,564
How could you even call that love?

820
00:49:46,442 --> 00:49:49,528
If it remains unspoken
and you ache in silence…

821
00:49:52,531 --> 00:49:55,367
as if your heart was being crushed
by some great boulder…

822
00:49:58,204 --> 00:50:00,414
that is not love.

823
00:50:14,428 --> 00:50:16,263
<i>Love, my foot.</i>

824
00:50:24,104 --> 00:50:26,357
<i>Unable to share</i>
<i>even a fraction of my feelings…</i>

825
00:50:29,652 --> 00:50:31,987
<i>I just rubbed some pebbles like an idiot</i>

826
00:50:32,071 --> 00:50:33,906
<i>and clenched my fists.</i>

827
00:50:52,967 --> 00:50:55,886
<i>Do you truly harbor affection for me?</i>

828
00:50:56,637 --> 00:50:57,555
<i>I do.</i>

829
00:50:58,347 --> 00:51:00,349
Screw this damn world,

830
00:51:00,432 --> 00:51:01,850
and let your heart flutter with me.

831
00:51:04,395 --> 00:51:06,355
Let me be your only one too.

832
00:51:08,774 --> 00:51:10,442
<i>That ends now.</i>

833
00:51:10,943 --> 00:51:12,486
<i>No more acting like a fool.</i>

834
00:51:14,321 --> 00:51:15,990
<i>I am done with that.</i>

835
00:51:28,210 --> 00:51:29,795
GEONGUK APOTHECARY

836
00:51:31,005 --> 00:51:33,924
Excuse me, shopkeeper.
Give me some medicinal herbs.

837
00:51:34,008 --> 00:51:37,553
Prepare the most precious
and expensive ones quickly.

838
00:51:40,764 --> 00:51:41,765
So?

839
00:51:42,349 --> 00:51:43,809
Do you have a spot for Se-gye?

840
00:51:43,892 --> 00:51:45,144
Yes, well…

841
00:51:45,686 --> 00:51:47,479
Creating a position is easy,

842
00:51:48,063 --> 00:51:49,982
but I'm worried about internal backlash.

843
00:51:50,065 --> 00:51:52,443
It'd be better for Se-gye
if he were welcomed back by all.

844
00:51:52,526 --> 00:51:53,611
It would look better too.

845
00:51:55,237 --> 00:51:57,156
Do you have a plan in mind?

846
00:51:57,239 --> 00:51:59,533
There is a position that remains unfilled.

847
00:52:00,576 --> 00:52:03,579
Why don't you let him handle
the US branch?

848
00:52:03,662 --> 00:52:06,540
If he proves his ability
and contributes to the company,

849
00:52:06,624 --> 00:52:08,417
the opposition will quickly die down.

850
00:52:09,960 --> 00:52:11,086
I see.

851
00:52:12,796 --> 00:52:13,797
I'll think about it.

852
00:52:18,302 --> 00:52:19,803
Why is this so watery?

853
00:52:19,887 --> 00:52:21,263
- What?
- It is completely watery.

854
00:52:21,347 --> 00:52:23,766
There are no herbs at all.
It is just full of plain water.

855
00:52:23,849 --> 00:52:25,059
Not plain water. A decoction.

856
00:52:25,142 --> 00:52:26,977
You must be talking about packaged herbs.

857
00:52:27,061 --> 00:52:30,064
Our clinic doesn't dispense
packaged herbs.

858
00:52:30,147 --> 00:52:32,608
It'd also be hard for you
to brew this yourself.

859
00:52:32,691 --> 00:52:35,903
So you mean
it has all been brewed already?

860
00:52:36,487 --> 00:52:37,780
Goodness me.

861
00:52:38,405 --> 00:52:40,699
Just the thought of squatting
to brew each packet

862
00:52:40,783 --> 00:52:42,826
had my knees aching.

863
00:52:42,910 --> 00:52:45,037
The world really has gotten better.

864
00:52:50,542 --> 00:52:51,960
Thanks.

865
00:52:58,342 --> 00:53:00,719
<i>Cha Se-gye, come here</i>
<i>as soon as you are done with work.</i>

866
00:53:00,803 --> 00:53:02,262
<i>I need to tell you something.</i>

867
00:53:02,888 --> 00:53:03,931
CHA SE-GYE: OKAY

868
00:53:05,182 --> 00:53:06,684
Why hide my feelings?

869
00:53:06,767 --> 00:53:08,727
No sense in letting them go to waste.

870
00:53:11,146 --> 00:53:12,481
Yes.

871
00:53:12,564 --> 00:53:15,192
My schedule changed.
I can't make it this weekend.

872
00:53:15,275 --> 00:53:18,112
Don't tell Seo-jun I'm coming just yet.

873
00:53:19,071 --> 00:53:21,365
I'll see how it goes and call you back.

874
00:53:46,807 --> 00:53:48,058
AIDE SEO

875
00:53:54,648 --> 00:53:57,943
<i>Sir, an announcement</i>
<i>has been posted on the intranet.</i>

876
00:54:14,251 --> 00:54:15,419
PERSONNEL APPOINTMENT NOTICE

877
00:54:15,502 --> 00:54:16,795
US BRANCH MANAGER
CHOI MUN-DO

878
00:54:29,308 --> 00:54:30,893
CHAIL GROUP CHAIRMAN CHA DAL-SU

879
00:54:39,860 --> 00:54:42,988
<i>Sir, we got a call</i>
<i>from that hospitalized nurse.</i>

880
00:54:43,071 --> 00:54:45,032
<i>She said she had something to tell you.</i>

881
00:54:51,121 --> 00:54:54,249
<i>I might be a bit late,</i>
<i>but I will be there eventually.</i>

882
00:55:27,282 --> 00:55:28,992
What brings you here this late?

883
00:55:37,668 --> 00:55:38,710
<i>Did you join a cult?</i>

884
00:55:38,794 --> 00:55:39,795
I'm off.

885
00:55:39,867 --> 00:55:41,046
CHOI MUN-DO, CHAIL E&C

886
00:55:54,059 --> 00:55:55,561
<i>I've been thinking about it too.</i>

887
00:55:55,644 --> 00:55:57,646
How desperate one must be
for the chairman's seat

888
00:55:57,729 --> 00:55:59,815
to resort to such pathetic stalking.

889
00:56:02,943 --> 00:56:03,819
Still,

890
00:56:05,112 --> 00:56:06,864
you shouldn't have broken the law.

891
00:56:06,947 --> 00:56:08,407
<i>I'm so sorry.</i>

892
00:56:08,490 --> 00:56:12,369
<i>Even if I was blinded by the money,</i>
<i>I should've never done as I was told.</i>

893
00:56:12,452 --> 00:56:15,497
<i>I swear I will pay for what I've done.</i>
<i>Just please spare my life.</i>

894
00:56:20,961 --> 00:56:22,212
So?

895
00:56:23,255 --> 00:56:25,632
Do you actually believe
you have leverage over me?

896
00:56:28,135 --> 00:56:30,095
I get that you're willing
to throw away your pride

897
00:56:30,178 --> 00:56:32,639
and risk your own life for this,

898
00:56:32,723 --> 00:56:34,016
but what about Seo-jun?

899
00:57:03,545 --> 00:57:04,880
Sure.

900
00:57:06,006 --> 00:57:08,842
Like you said,
I made extreme sacrifices to get here.

901
00:57:08,926 --> 00:57:10,302
And what about you?

902
00:57:10,385 --> 00:57:11,803
What exactly have you done?

903
00:57:13,639 --> 00:57:15,891
All you ever did was mess up

904
00:57:15,974 --> 00:57:17,935
and abuse your power.

905
00:57:19,061 --> 00:57:20,562
Do you think you're qualified?

906
00:57:27,527 --> 00:57:28,487
Forget it.

907
00:57:29,947 --> 00:57:31,031
Let's just stop here.

908
00:57:52,094 --> 00:57:53,178
What are you doing?

909
00:57:53,261 --> 00:57:55,097
I have something to show you too.

910
00:58:15,993 --> 00:58:17,202
What is this?

911
00:58:17,911 --> 00:58:19,913
Why don't you ask her yourself?

912
00:58:20,455 --> 00:58:22,332
When a man and a woman
get together in secret,

913
00:58:22,416 --> 00:58:23,834
what do you think is going on?

914
00:58:23,917 --> 00:58:25,419
Don't make me laugh.

915
00:58:25,502 --> 00:58:28,255
What would someone like you do
with a woman like her?

916
00:58:28,338 --> 00:58:30,757
You obviously brought these,
thinking you could somehow test me.

917
00:58:30,841 --> 00:58:33,051
You have a lot of faith in her.

918
00:58:33,135 --> 00:58:35,345
Who knows what kind of deal was made?

919
00:58:40,183 --> 00:58:42,310
You seem to be
under some grave misconception.

920
00:58:42,394 --> 00:58:43,937
Too bad.

921
00:58:44,021 --> 00:58:46,481
As if I'd ever get involved
with someone like her.

922
00:58:49,860 --> 00:58:52,070
Maybe it could work on Uncle?

923
00:58:53,071 --> 00:58:54,322
"Someone like her"?

924
00:58:55,449 --> 00:58:57,117
That old man is still heartbroken

925
00:58:57,200 --> 00:58:59,828
over his one and only precious son,

926
00:58:59,911 --> 00:59:02,831
who threw his life away
for the wrong woman.

927
00:59:02,914 --> 00:59:03,874
I wonder

928
00:59:04,374 --> 00:59:05,876
how he'll view Shin Seo-ri.

929
00:59:09,087 --> 00:59:12,382
You know better than anyone
what Uncle did to your mom.

930
00:59:12,466 --> 00:59:14,009
You must be insane.

931
00:59:16,303 --> 00:59:17,721
Yeah.

932
00:59:18,889 --> 00:59:20,807
That's what vulnerability gets you.

933
00:59:20,891 --> 00:59:23,935
People naturally grow weaker
the more they have to lose.

934
00:59:24,519 --> 00:59:27,564
Give up on returning to the company,
and I won't interfere.

935
00:59:28,148 --> 00:59:31,109
And of course,
Uncle will never need to know any of this.

936
00:59:41,578 --> 00:59:42,496
Damn it.

937
00:59:53,548 --> 00:59:56,301
DAEBAK BOARDING HOUSE

938
01:00:01,640 --> 01:00:02,808
What is this?

939
01:00:03,308 --> 01:00:04,726
He said he would be late.

940
01:00:04,810 --> 01:00:05,769
Jeez.

941
01:00:07,187 --> 01:00:08,438
Cha Se-gye.

942
01:00:09,397 --> 01:00:10,899
You said you would be late.

943
01:00:19,116 --> 01:00:20,742
It's late. Where were you?

944
01:00:20,826 --> 01:00:23,703
Yeah, I had to take care of something.

945
01:00:26,039 --> 01:00:29,126
I've had a headache all day
because of the bomb you dropped.

946
01:00:29,209 --> 01:00:30,627
And yet you look completely fine.

947
01:00:30,710 --> 01:00:32,003
How draining for me.

948
01:00:35,340 --> 01:00:36,633
Cha Se-gye, about that--

949
01:00:36,716 --> 01:00:39,386
After I listened to your nonsense,

950
01:00:39,469 --> 01:00:41,054
I was made a fool of.

951
01:00:41,138 --> 01:00:42,430
Yet here I am anyway.

952
01:00:44,391 --> 01:00:45,892
I somehow crawled back here.

953
01:00:45,976 --> 01:00:47,018
No.

954
01:00:47,102 --> 01:00:47,978
I just--

955
01:00:48,061 --> 01:00:50,438
Do you really have
that little faith in me?

956
01:00:53,942 --> 01:00:55,902
I hoped we wouldn't have any secrets.

957
01:00:56,528 --> 01:00:57,737
I heard you met Choi Mun-do.

958
01:00:58,655 --> 01:01:00,991
- Why didn't you tell me?
- Well, that is--

959
01:01:01,074 --> 01:01:03,034
I heard he offered you some sort of deal.

960
01:01:03,118 --> 01:01:04,536
You should have told me.

961
01:01:04,619 --> 01:01:07,330
Whatever it is, I can do more for you.

962
01:01:08,915 --> 01:01:12,169
I thought I gave you
enough reason to trust me…

963
01:01:14,546 --> 01:01:16,214
but I guess I didn't.

964
01:01:16,298 --> 01:01:18,258
How much more do I have to do?

965
01:01:19,593 --> 01:01:22,429
How much longer
must I cling to you and grovel

966
01:01:22,512 --> 01:01:23,722
for you to open up?

967
01:01:26,183 --> 01:01:29,561
If you don't feel the same way,
I'd rather you just use me openly.

968
01:01:30,061 --> 01:01:32,606
I'm more than willing to let you use me.

969
01:01:46,411 --> 01:01:47,579
Yeah.

970
01:01:48,788 --> 01:01:50,582
This is the Shin Seo-ri I know.

971
01:01:52,584 --> 01:01:54,794
If you really are that ruthless
as you claim,

972
01:01:56,338 --> 01:01:58,381
don't half-heartedly pretend
to be a decent person.

973
01:01:58,465 --> 01:02:00,258
Stop worrying about me.

974
01:02:00,342 --> 01:02:02,594
Just think about yourself

975
01:02:03,261 --> 01:02:05,847
if you're going to play the villain!

976
01:02:10,852 --> 01:02:12,938
Then commit to it.

977
01:02:17,234 --> 01:02:18,109
Let go.

978
01:02:18,193 --> 01:02:19,194
Let go!

979
01:02:19,903 --> 01:02:20,946
Let go!

980
01:02:21,655 --> 01:02:24,324
Let go of me! Let go!

981
01:02:24,824 --> 01:02:25,784
Let go!

982
01:02:58,191 --> 01:02:59,317
I can't…

983
01:03:00,568 --> 01:03:03,029
think straight for even a moment
thanks to you.

984
01:03:13,081 --> 01:03:14,791
Whoever you are…

985
01:03:17,836 --> 01:03:19,629
wherever you came from…

986
01:03:22,007 --> 01:03:23,341
I believe it all.

987
01:03:24,009 --> 01:03:24,926
What?

988
01:03:26,428 --> 01:03:28,805
Yeah. I believe whatever you say…

989
01:03:30,765 --> 01:03:32,475
so just keep your eyes on me.

990
01:03:36,604 --> 01:03:39,065
Forget all those other bastards
and just look at me.

991
01:03:43,528 --> 01:03:44,571
Please.

992
01:04:33,745 --> 01:04:37,374
MY ROYAL NEMESIS

993
01:05:04,484 --> 01:05:05,652
<i>We're done testing the waters?</i>

994
01:05:05,735 --> 01:05:07,904
- Let us go on a date, Cha Se-gye.
- All of a sudden?

995
01:05:07,987 --> 01:05:10,698
<i>I am going to be beyond generous.</i>

996
01:05:10,782 --> 01:05:13,201
<i>You're my Seo-ri's boyfriend?</i>

997
01:05:13,284 --> 01:05:14,369
<i>Please forgive me.</i>

998
01:05:14,452 --> 01:05:16,830
<i>We're looking at a leadership change.</i>

999
01:05:16,913 --> 01:05:18,832
<i>The young master just arrived</i>
<i>at the head office.</i>

1000
01:05:18,915 --> 01:05:21,042
<i>Do you honestly think</i>
<i>I'll just step down quietly?</i>

1001
01:05:21,126 --> 01:05:24,754
- Have you seen the patient in Room 12?
- You sure you can handle that?

1002
01:05:24,838 --> 01:05:27,924
<i>Luring and threatening</i>
<i>a helpless old woman?</i>

1003
01:05:28,007 --> 01:05:29,968
You have nothing to lose, Ms. Shin.

1004
01:05:30,051 --> 01:05:32,846
I hate seeing you involved
with Choi Mun-do. I hate it!

1005
01:05:32,929 --> 01:05:35,098
You are even worse than him.
You are even more hurtful!

1006
01:05:35,181 --> 01:05:38,393
I want Se-gye to end up
with someone who has love to spare.

1007
01:05:38,476 --> 01:05:41,020
<i>Shin Seo-ri, just pick up your phone.</i>

1008
01:05:42,858 --> 01:05:44,858
Subtitle translation by Justin S. Kim
